title: Yusof Ishak
summary: Tun Haji Inche' Yusof bin Ishak DUT (First Class), SMN, KStJ (/ˈjʊsɒf bɪn ˈɪshɑːk/ YUUSS-off bin ISS-hahk; Jawi: يوسف بن إسحاق‎; 12 August 1910 – 23 November 1970) was a Singaporean politician who was the first President of Singapore elected by the Parliament of Singapore, serving from 1965 to 1970.
